cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.CR, cs.SY 

The paper proposes a new algorithmic framework for training neural networks that are verifiable, which falls under the broad category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of the framework for tasks such as image classification (cs.CV) and robustness to adversarial examples (cs.CR). Additionally, the paper involves the use of both predictor and verifier networks, which is a common technique in the field of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper discusses the optimization of a weighted combination of loss terms, which is a common technique in the field of control systems (cs.SY).
